# Academic AI Automation Kit - Google Colab
# 🎓 Quick Start Guide

## 1. Setup
Run the following cell to install dependencies and clone the repository.

```python
!pip install transformers torch sentencepiece gradio pydantic
!git clone https://github.com/pusakamediaid-dotcom/academic-ai-automation-kit.git
%cd academic-ai-automation-kit
```

## 2. Launch the Interface
Run this cell to start the Gradio Web UI.

```python
!python app.py
```
Click the `public URL` generated by Gradio to open the interface.

## 3. Using the Tool
1. Paste your academic text into the text area.
2. Select your preferred mode (Short, Detailed, Insights, or Notes).
3. Click **Process Text**.
4. Copy the Markdown result directly into your Notion or Obsidian vault.
